<h2>All 14 Zones from Sonic 3 &amp; Knuckles</h2>

A.I.R. includes <strong>every zone from both Sonic 3 and Sonic &amp; Knuckles</strong>, played as one continuous adventure the way it was originally intended. Each zone features unique mechanics, multiple paths depending on your character, and boss encounters:

<strong>Sonic 3 zones:</strong> Angel Island, Hydrocity, Marble Garden, Carnival Night, Ice Cap, and Launch Base (with Big Arm re-enabled as Sonic 3's true final boss).

<strong>Sonic &amp; Knuckles zones:</strong> Mushroom Hill, Flying Battery, Sandopolis, Lava Reef, Hidden Palace, Sky Sanctuary, Death Egg, and The Doomsday Zone.

All three characters — <strong>Sonic, Tails, and Knuckles</strong> — play through different paths with their unique abilities. Knuckles has entirely different boss fights and route options. And for the first time, you can play as the <strong>Knuckles &amp; Tails team</strong>, a combination that was never available in the original game.

<h2>Sonic 3 A.I.R. Mods</h2>

One of A.I.R.'s biggest strengths is its <strong>robust mod support</strong>. The modding community has created everything from character swaps (Shadow, Silver, Cream, Rouge, and many more) to complete visual overhauls and gameplay transformations.

We have a dedicated section with <strong>20+ mods</strong> ready to download — check out our full <a href="/3-air/mods/">Sonic 3 A.I.R. Mods collection</a> to browse character packs, sprite replacements, and gameplay tweaks.

<h2>Sonic 3 A.I.R. FAQ</h2>

<div class="details-grid">
<details>
<summary>Is Sonic 3 A.I.R. free?</summary>
<p>Yes, completely free and open source. The source code is available on <a href="https://github.com/Eukaryot/sonic3air" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">GitHub</a>.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Do I need the original ROM to play?</summary>
<p>Yes. Sonic 3 A.I.R. requires the original Sonic 3 &amp; Knuckles ROM file (<code>Sonic_Knuckles_wSonic3.bin</code>) to run. The project provides an <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1oSud8dJHvdfrYbkGCfllAOp3JuTks7z4K5SwtVkXkx0/edit" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">official list of legal alternatives</a> for obtaining it.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I play Sonic 3 A.I.R. on Android?</summary>
<p>Yes. Download the APK from the <a href="https://sonic3air.org/android/android.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">official Android page</a> and transfer the ROM file to your device. Loading times may be longer on low-end devices.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How do I install mods?</summary>
<p>Place mod files in the <code>mods</code> folder inside your Sonic 3 A.I.R. directory. Enable them from the in-game mods menu. Browse our <a href="/3-air/mods/">mods collection</a> for ready-to-download options.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is this better than Sonic Origins?</summary>
<p>Both are great options. Sonic Origins is the official Sega remaster, while A.I.R. is a fan project offering significantly more customization options, mod support, and configurability. Many fans use both.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Does it work on iOS?</summary>
<p>An iOS/Web beta is available through <a href="https://projects.sappharad.com/s3air_ios/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Sappharad's port</a>, though it may have stability limitations compared to the desktop and Android versions.</p>
</details>
</div>

